Added better i18n support (#115)

- Localization is now exposed inside the widget itself
- "language" is now exposed as a config option
  - Can be a languageCode, i.e. "en", "ja", etc
  - Can be a function that returns a languageCode. The list of supported
    languages and user languages are passed to this hook.
- If no "language" option is passed, defaults to the user's browser settings
- Will pull languages by default from the Okta CDN, but can be overridden
  by the new "assets.baseUrl" and "assets.rewrite" options
- Deprecated "labels" and "country" and replaced with a new "i18n" option
  which also handles overriding on a per language level
- Support for developers adding their own languages through the "i18n" option
- Generates a new jsonp label dist type for easy CORS consumption

Other:
- Generates config file with version & supported languages
- Some updates to make it easier to run test specs on their own
- New deprecate util function
- Because the locale can now be updated dynamically, several code patterns
  needed to be changed. Most commonly - calling our Okta.loc function when
  the module is being evaluated.

Created npm dist file which does not include thirdparty deps (#123)

* Created npm dist file which does not include thirdparty deps

Now, when going through the npm flow with require('@okta/okta-signin-widget'),
the file that is required is much smaller, and will not include thirdparty
dependencies. This allows the consumer to use their own versions of deps like
jquery, underscore, backbone, etc.

Other:
- Simplified Gruntfile copy, build, and prerelease commands, and sped up
  build by moving to parallel webpack config execution of release flow
- Moved more vendor files from source to npm:
  - jquery-placeholder
  - qtip2
  - xdomain
- Updated e2e test harness logic to use Handlebars partials
- Moved e2e tests from testing dev version to testing CDN and npm versions
- Fixed bug where we were including files from courage that we were trying
  to ignore (relative paths do not work with alias)

fix: webauthn enroll and verify fix on v1

* Webauthn enroll and verify now works on v1 in safari on bigsur and ios13.
* The change to verify flow is common across all browsers to make sure we are future proof and follow security best practices ( explicit user click before webauthn prompt)

* This needs upgrade of auth js to 4.6.0 to consume fix that uses browser fetch instead of cross fetch as
    cross fetch wraps fetch with unnecessary promises causing safari to think the call is programatic and not due to direct user interaction
    even if webauthn prompt is triggered on api callback after user click.

 - upgrades grunt-sass to next minor version
 - adds sass (dart sass), the official Sass recommended compiler https://sass-lang.com/dart-sass

 - changes the configurations in gruntfile.js to use the recommended standards to parse scss into css by grunt-sass https://github.com/sindresorhus/grunt-sass
